      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_GetUserRolesByEmail",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve the roles associated with a user based on their email address. It queries several tables related to membership and roles within a database, specifically targeting the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Membership",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Users",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_UsersInRoles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Roles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " tables. The procedure returns a list of roles (RoleId and RoleName) for the user whose email matches the provided input parameter."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a series of inner joins across four tables to fetch the desired data. The logic is simple, with a single SELECT statement and no conditional logic or loops."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
